30
00:01:44.573 --> 00:01:48.197
Is your interview tooling
totally inaccessible,

31
00:01:48.197 --> 00:01:51.323
cuz that's the first barrier right there.

32
00:01:51.323 --> 00:01:57.715
There's barriers throughout the work
life cycle, but that first door,

33
00:01:57.715 --> 00:02:03.093
if you can't even apply for
a job, that's discrimination.

34
00:02:03.093 --> 00:02:05.349
Kind of a big word,
that's really what this is.

35
00:02:05.349 --> 00:02:08.557
So this isn't a statistics thing only,
this is like,

36
00:02:08.557 --> 00:02:12.418
people with disabilities are literally
shut out of the process.

37
00:02:12.418 --> 00:02:17.162
And so it's common but sometimes you're
in a place to do something about it.

38
00:02:17.162 --> 00:02:19.096
So here's a quick story.

39
00:02:19.096 --> 00:02:24.703
When I worked at a past company, I saw
some of our products that we were using,

40
00:02:24.703 --> 00:02:29.279
cloud services and things for
HR, like performance reviews,

41
00:02:29.279 --> 00:02:33.368
