it was easy to spot these issues.

42
00:02:33.368 --> 00:02:35.024
I mean, I was using it all the time.

43
00:02:35.024 --> 00:02:36.723
I was a manager at the time.

44
00:02:36.723 --> 00:02:40.420
And so I provided product feedback
to both of those companies.

45
00:02:40.420 --> 00:02:44.737
Like, hey, here's a prioritized
list of issues for you.

46
00:02:44.737 --> 00:02:48.725
One of the companies was so eager to fix
that stuff that we got on a call and

47
00:02:48.725 --> 00:02:52.202
they were like, more, give us more,
please, we love this.

48
00:02:52.202 --> 00:02:53.085
Awesome.

49
00:02:53.085 --> 00:02:55.912
The other company, crickets.

50
00:02:55.912 --> 00:02:58.989
So sometimes you can make
a difference with this stuff,

51
00:02:58.989 --> 00:03:00.503
people are really into it.

52
00:03:00.503 --> 00:03:05.365
Sometimes it's just like throwing
your feedback into the garbage can,

53
00:03:05.365 --> 00:03:06.566
unfortunately.

54
00:03:06.566 --> 00:03:12.052
But you might be able to influence
procurement at your company if there's

55
00:03:12.052 --> 00:03:17.016
a more accessible alternative to
something, just be aware of it.

56
00:03:17.016 --> 00:03:22.233
It might be outside the scope of your
role, especially a big companies.

57
00:03:22.233 --> 00:03:27.167
But this kind of elephant in
the room with accessibility is like,

58
00:03:27.167 --> 00:03:31.024
we don't wanna just work
to make accessibility for

59
00:03:31.024 --> 00:03:35.250
people, we want true inclusion and
true civil rights.

60
00:03:35.250 --> 00:03:38.229
That's where we wanna get to.

61
00:03:38.229 --> 00:03:41.862
On that note,
centering people with disabilities.

62
00:03:41.862 --> 00:03:44.352
This goes beyond hiring.

63
00:03:44.352 --> 00:03:48.917
This is getting back to
product development also.

64
00:03:48.917 --> 00:03:52.600
So we wanna remember what this is about.

65
00:03:52.600 --> 00:03:57.193
We don't wanna get caught up in just
like being accessibility technicians.

66
00:03:57.193 --> 00:04:04.117
So there is a phrase in accessibility,
nothing about us without us.

67
00:04:04.117 --> 00:04:08.046
We've been doing a lot of talking
about accessibility today, so

68
00:04:08.046 --> 00:04:11.770
it is a little bit ironic to me
that I'm saying this right now.

69
00:04:11.770 --> 00:04:15.726
But I just wanna share this with you so
that we can try and

70
00:04:15.726 --> 00:04:20.371
open doorways in our work to
involve people with disabilities,

71
00:04:20.371 --> 00:04:23.741
to join our teams,
to consult with our teams.

72
00:04:23.741 --> 00:04:26.683
We're gonna pay people for their time.

73
00:04:26.683 --> 00:04:29.726
There is a book here called
Nothing About Us Without Us,

74
00:04:29.726 --> 00:04:33.052
