have worked to gain their rights.

77
00:04:40.606 --> 00:04:44.492
A lot of our history in the US is
because of this activist history,

78
00:04:44.492 --> 00:04:45.914
it's pretty awesome.

79
00:04:45.914 --> 00:04:48.534
But it sucks that people had to do that.

80
00:04:48.534 --> 00:04:50.965
They had to really fight for that.

81
00:04:50.965 --> 00:04:54.250
And in some ways,
it's a lot easier for us on the web,

82
00:04:54.250 --> 00:04:57.110
we can just redesign stuff and
rebuild stuff.

83
00:04:57.110 --> 00:04:59.660
It's like we don't have to knock down,

84
00:04:59.660 --> 00:05:04.618
we don't have to demolish a building to
make more accessible entrances to it.

85
00:05:04.618 --> 00:05:06.034
But there are some analogs.

86
00:05:06.034 --> 00:05:09.526
Depending on how
foundational the issues are,

87
00:05:09.526 --> 00:05:13.199
we might need to tear down the site and
start over.

88
00:05:13.199 --> 00:05:17.795
But with technology it
is slightly different.

89
00:05:17.795 --> 00:05:20.774
So yeah, we wanna advocate for
accessibility or

90
00:05:20.774 --> 00:05:24.780
people with disabilities to be
involved earlier in the process.

